Chief Financial Officer Job (Polyester Manufacturing), Tangerang, Indonesia  -
Chief Financial Officer Job (Polyester Manufacturing), Tangerang, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the largest polyester manufacturing and distribution companies in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a financial management professional, ideally a registered accountant, for the job of Chief Financial Officer, to be based in Tangerang, Indonesia. Substantial experience with mergers and acquisitions, and/or IPOs, is preferred. The successful candidate will be working closely with the Director of the Company and will ensure that all finance, administrative and development processes are running optimally. This is an excellent opening for a professional executive with a leading company. Key responsibilities will include: Develop financial strategies and action plansDrive strategic financial vision and all corporate finance activities which include leading the company's "IPO program" and scaling the organization for rapid expansionOversee the finance, accounting and all administration process and reportingAssisting CEO in analysing new business development, feasibility studies and liaises with all related parties including financial institutions, principals, to start up the new developed businessSet up and oversee all financial KPI’s of each subsidiary and establish action plansDealing with banks or other financial institutionsOversee the management and coordination of all fiscal reporting activitiesOversee cash flow of all subsidiariesEstablish and developing the right system information to support the business Job Requirements Bachelor’s degree in economics, finance or accounting from reputable universityCPA (Certified Public Accountant)Substantial experience with mergers and acquisitions, and/or IPOs5 years’ experience as head of finance and accounting (senior manager level)Experience dealing & establishing financial facilities from banksFinancial reporting analysis expertEnglish fluencyComputer literacyGood communication and leadership skills All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to industrial@monroeconsulting.com
